    {
      "name": "Socket.io Events",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Socket Events Documentation",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:5000/health",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": [
                "localhost"
              ],
              "port": "5000",
              "path": [
                "health"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Socket.io events are real-time and don't use HTTP requests. Use the HTML files to test:\n\n**Client → Server Events:**\n1. user-join\n   - Data: { userId, userType, userName }\n   - Emits: user-online event to all clients\n\n2. send-message\n   - Data: { chatId, senderId, senderType, senderName, receiverId, message, timestamp }\n   - Emits: receive-message event to all clients\n\n3. typing\n   - Data: { chatId, userName, userType }\n   - Broadcasts: user-typing event\n\n4. stop-typing\n   - Data: { chatId }\n   - Broadcasts: user-stop-typing event\n\n**Server → Client Events:**\n1. receive-message\n   - Returns: Full message object with metadata\n\n2. user-online\n   - Returns: User info and list of all online users\n\n3. user-offline\n   - Returns: User info who went offline\n\n4. user-typing\n   - Returns: Info about who is typing\n\n5. user-stop-typing\n   - Returns: Info about who stopped typing"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
